This change addresses a couple bugs in the roaming toggle tests and

improves them via more descriptive names of certain variables. The

issues that were addressed are:

object instead of the policy value.

entry.title: [IP Protection] Make NSPAL and config cache non-null in proxy delegate
entry.content:
When code was moved from NetworkServiceProxyDelegate to

IpProtectionProxyDelegate, the historical nullability of the

network_service_proxy_allow_list_ and ipp_config_cache_ fields was

carried over. These fields no longer make sense being null as the

IpProtectionProxyDelegate is guarded behind the MaskedDomainList

feature, and a config cache is created specifically for use by the

IpProtectionProxyDelegate.



This change enforces and makes it clear that these fields cannot be

null.

entry.title: Fully implement bidi for a line's trailing spaces (UAX#9 L1)
entry.content:
Per UAX#9 L1, any spaces that after line breaking would fall logically

at the end of a line must be reset to the paragraph's initial

embedding level, regardless of the embedding level of those spaces in

the paragraph. Until now, Blink only had partial support for this.



The reason this was hard to implement in Blink is because the

direction of text is computed in a per-paragraph level, splitting the

text into items with a given direction and embedding level. Those

items are then split into item results when line breaking, but item

results must have the same direction as the item.



As part of line breaking, some item results are produced which only

have trailing spaces. The partial support, implemented in

crrev.com/c/2505486, consisted of marking these results with the

`has_only_trailing_spaces` flag, and using this flag to distinguish

them when reordering the item results.



This patch builds on top of that partial fix by adding a final

processing step to line breaking, which splits item results so that

trailing spaces (with a different embedding level as the paragraph)

are split into its own item result, and by marking all trailing spaces

item results as `has_only_trailing_spaces`.



This also fixes bug 1514753, where having a item result with non-base

direction which had logically trailing spaces was causing the text

(rather than the spaces) to hang, because

`LineInfo::ComputeTrailingSpaceWidth` assumed that UAX#9 L1 held.



This patch also modifies some existing WPT tests to make them use a

monospace Arabic webfont (since it's not guaranteed that all OS's have

one), and by changing the widths slightly to work around bug 1409445.

entry.title: Split PDM address writing logic from PDM
entry.content:
Moves address add/update/remove functionality from the PDM to the ADM:

- AddProfile(), UpdateProfile(). The implementation is moved to the ADM.

In the PDM, the functions are kept, but they simply forward the call

to the ADM. This way, not a million callers need to change (for now).

- RemoveProfile(): Like above, but the function is removed from the PDM,

since it was only called from this class. Everyone outside the PDM

uses RemoveByGUID() (which eventually will need to be split).

- The queueing logic of pending modifications: Moved completely out of

the PDM. In particular, the ADM becomes the WebDataService's

AutofillProfileChangedCallback instead of the PDM. This way, it is

notified whenever a modification has finished.

- As described in go/split-pdm, in order to deal with the observers

later, a callback to the PDM's NotifyPersonalDataObserver() is passed

to the ADM. This way, the ADM can notify the PDM's observers whenever

a modification finishes. (This intentionally avoids exposing the

entire PDM to the ADM)



All the code is moved without changes.

entry.title: [cc] Allow reclaim of <canvas> resources outside the viewport
entry.content:
With canvas hibernation (enabled on most platforms), when a 2D canvas is

part of a background page, its backing TextureLayer is cleared, allowing

GPU-side memory to be freed. Unfortunately, this doesn't work, since

there is a reference to the previous texture held in the active tree,

impl-side.



A recent change

(https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5063730)

allows these resources to be freed when compositor frame eviction

happens, i.e. when viz returns the resources. However, as noted in

crbug.com/1516888, this does not apply to resources that haven't been

imported into viz. This means that all elements that are not in

the viewport at the time where the page gets backgrounded are not

evicted by this path, or any other (it makes sense, since theh CL above

relies on viz returning resources, and it cannot return a resource it

doesn't know about).



This CL addresses the case of these canvases. It was observed to happen

on google docs for instance, which uses 2D canvas for its rendering, but

should apply more broadly (e.g. with canvas-based ads that are outside

the viewport). Potential savings on high resolution screens are >10MiB

per google docs tab (and similar sites).

entry.title: Don't override OnSyncShutdown() in PDM
entry.content:
OnSyncShutdown() is called when the synce keyed service shuts down. The

PDM already unregisters its observers in PDM::Shutdown(), which is

called before the sync service's Shutdown(), since the PDM depends on

the sync service. As such, the code is a no-op outside tests.



Some tests create a TestSyncService which is shorter lived than the

PDM. In those cases, unregistering the observer before the sync service

dies using OnSyncShutdown() was necessary. These tests are changed to

use a TestSyncService with longer lifetime than the PDM.

entry.title: Split PDM address reading logic from PDM
entry.content:
See go/split-pdm. This CL creates an AddressDataManager (ADM) class,

which is for now owned by the PDM. All address related _reading_ logic

is moved over:

- The synced_local_profiles_ and account_profiles_ member variables,

which store copies of the data in the DB.

- LoadProfiles(), which posts read requests on the WebDataService.

- WebDataServiceConsumer, which receives the result once a read request

has finished and populates the member variables.

- GetProfiles(FromSource)() and GetProfileByGUID(), which can be used to

read the member variables.

- Functions around checking whether read queries are pending and around

cancelling them.

- Logging metrics once the first read has finished.



On the PDM side, the public functions are kept - but implemented by

calling the implementation in the ADM. Private/protected functions are

removed from the PDM. Refresh() is updated to call the ADM

implementation.



The implementation is copied over without changes - except for

OnWebDataServiceRequestDone(), because the PDM implementation handles

address and payments logic there.

In the header file, some of the comments are updated.



Follow-up CLs will move the remaining logic over.

entry.title: Make --force-search-engine-choice-screen stop multi-prompting
entry.content:
Changes the way the flag works: instead of allowing to skip some of

the checks done when we try to determine whether a profile should be

triggering the choice screen, it just clears the prefs associated

with marking the choice as made when the service is constructed.



This is intended to make the user experience when using this flag

more representative of the actual behaviour, instead of triggering

multiple times the prompt, which can mask potential triggering logic

issues.



Important note: if the feature is configured to only prompt new

profiles, this flag will not force-prompt existing ones either! So

overriding the feature param state will still be needed.
